Since we'll be uploading the video to other sources, we should have a option so the user can choose which streaming service to use or download the video directly. So have a button for Youtube, Vimeo, linux.org, archive.org, etc

Example of the data:
```
{
  ...
  "videos": [
    {
      "url": "http://s3.us.archive.org/ndvchipy/Who_saved_The_Onion_from_being.mp4", 
      "length": null, 
      "type": "mp4"
    }, 
    {
      "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dXTtcs6DrzY", 
      "length": 0, 
      "type": "youtube"
    }
  ], 
  ...
}

```

Looking at the original data I don't see a field for marking the original video so we'll need to add that in. I'm thinking it could just be added into the object in the `videos` array. eg: (thoughts?)

 ```
{
  ...
  "videos": [
    {
      "url": "http://s3.us.archive.org/ndvchipy/Who_saved_The_Onion_from_being.mp4", 
      "length": null, 
      "type": "mp4",
      "original": true
    }, 
    {
      "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dXTtcs6DrzY", 
      "length": 0, 
      "type": "youtube",
      "original": false
    }
  ], 
  ...
}

```

At first this field won't exist. Maybe just choose the first in the list? -shrug-
In the future we also might have a torrent file they can download as well.

